Welcome To Triaxis Install Guide
This Guide Will Help You To Install Triaxis Correctly
(NOTE Triaxis Only Supports Intel or AMD Architecture Which Triaxis Doesn't Support ARM architecture)

1 enter https://ubuntu.com/download/server then download ubuntu server lts iso then Before You Install Flash Ubuntu Server Iso With Rufus Etcher Or Ventoy
Make Sure That There Are No important Files Inside the USB Drive Then Backup Your Data On Your System Because It Will Erase Your Partition Drive After Installing Triaxis
For Rufus There are both ISO mode (the default, file-copy method) and DD mode (a block-level copy method) options
and I Would Recommend To Use dd mode Because On ISO mode it Can fail Because ISO mode partitions and formats the USB like a standard drive

2 Boot from the Ubuntu Server ISO (or Triaxis bootstrap ISO if available).
  Theres Password on su -
  I Would recommend to change the password to your password using sudo passwd root for example triaxis or become root using sudo -i
  Press Ctrl+Alt+F2 to switch to a shell.
3 Partition the Disk Using cfdisk fdisk parted etc
  cfdisk /dev/sda
  Create partitions:

4 EFI (if UEFI): 512MB, type EFI System.
  Root (/): rest of disk, type Linux filesystem.
  Swap: optional, type Linux swap.
  Write changes and quit.

5 Format Partitions
  mkfs.ext4 /dev/sda2     # root
  mkswap /dev/sda3        # swap
  mkfs.fat -F32 /dev/sda1 # EFI (if UEFI)

6 Mount Target System
  mount /dev/sda2 /mnt
  mkdir /mnt/boot
  mkdir /mnt/boot/efi
  mount /dev/sda1 /mnt/boot/efi
  swapon /dev/sda3

7 Bootstrap Base System
  debootstrap --arch amd64 focal /mnt http://archive.ubuntu.com/ubuntu

8 Chroot Into New System

  mount --bind /dev /mnt/dev
  mount --bind /proc /mnt/proc
  mount --bind /sys /mnt/sys
  chroot /mnt

9 Configure System
  Inside chroot:
  echo "myhostname" > /etc/hostname
  nano /etc/hosts   # add 127.0.0.1 myhostname

10 Set up networking:
   apt install net-tools ifupdown

11 Install Kernel & Essentials
   apt install linux-image-generic grub-pc sudo vim

12 Install Bootloader
   For BIOS:
   grub-install /dev/sda
   update-grub

13 For UEFI:
   apt install grub-efi
   grub-install --target=x86_64-efi --efi-directory=/boot/efi --bootloader-id=ubuntu
   update-grub

14 Create User
   adduser yourname
   usermod -aG sudo yourname

15 Exit & Reboot
   exit
   umount -R /mnt
   swapoff -a
   reboot

16 Update Using sudo apt update
17 Install Kde Plasma Desktop sudo apt install kde-standard for base and servers dont install desktop environment if you Want Other Desktop Environment Go To https://github.com/Haikal02-alt/Triaxis-GNU-Linux/blob/main/Other%20Desktop%20Environment
   After You Install KDE Plasma Run these commands
   sudo systemctl enable sddm
   sudo systemctl start sddm
Change Grub If You Need It Run sudo nano /etc/default/grub then
GRUB_TIMEOUT=0
Change them to:
GRUB_TIMEOUT_STYLE=menu
GRUB_TIMEOUT=5
update grub using sudo update-grub
18 Change GRUB Distributor Name Ubuntu To Triaxis Change it to: GRUB_DISTRIBUTOR="Triaxis GNU/Linux"
Then Update grub using sudo update-grub
19 enable submenu sudo nano /etc/grub.d/10_linux then change GRUB_DISABLE_SUBMENU="true" to GRUB_DISABLE_SUBMENU="false" then sudo update-grub
20 Add A logo use figlet to install it use sudo apt install figlet then figlet TRI then press prt sc then click rectangular region then screenshot the TRI on figlet then name it to triaxis-logo.png then move the image to /usr/share/pixmaps/ sudo cp ~/your TRI Logo/triaxis-logo.png /usr/share/pixmaps/
Or Install firefox or konqueror Then You Can Download Triaxis Logo On Readme then theres a triaxis logo then Save Image As /home/yourname/Pictures then name it to Triaxis-logo.png then Open a terminal.
Use the mv command with sudo:
sudo mv /home/yourname/Picture/Triaxis-logo.png /usr/share/pixmaps/
then sudo cp /usr/share/pixmaps/Triaxis-logo.png /usr/share/pixmaps/ubuntu-logo.svg
then sudo cp /usr/share/pixmaps/Triaxis-logo.png /usr/share/pixmaps/ubuntu-logo-text.png
then sudo cp /usr/share/pixmaps/Triaxis-logo.png /usr/share/pixmaps/ubuntu-logo-text-dark.png
the open sudo nano /etc/os-release then you find logo= then Change to LOGO=/usr/share/pixmaps/Triaxis-logo.png
if you cant see the change logo heres a guided version then follow the capital word
1 GO TO sudo nano /etc/os-release
2 THEN CHANGE LOGO=ubuntu-logo TO LOGO=/usr/share/pixmaps/Triaxis-logo.png
3 THEN CTRL X Y ENTER
Configure Plymouth Run sudo nano /etc/default/grub then if you see GRUB_CMDLINE_LINUX_DEFAULT="" Change it to GRUB_CMDLINE_LINUX_DEFAULT="quiet splash" ctrl x then y then enter then sudo update-grub
Then sudo nano /usr/share/plymouth/themes/ubuntu-text/ubuntu-text.plymouth Then Change title=Ubuntu 24.04 to title=Triaxis GNU/Linux Ctrl X Y Enter Then sudo update-initramfs -u
Then Reboot
Warning Some Text Might Have Different Fonts Or Changed To Another Font

21 Replace The SDDM Use sudo apt install sddm-theme-lubuntu Locate Available SDDM Themes If you’re getting “Permission denied” when trying to change SDDM to use the LXQt theme, it usually means you don’t have the right privileges or the file isn’t writable by your user. Here’s how to fix it:
Run sudo nano /etc/sddm.conf If the file doesn’t exist, create it with root Generate a default config: sudo sddm --example-config > /etc/sddm.conf then edit it sudo nano /etc/sddm.conf Set LXQt theme in the config
Inside /etc/sddm.conf, add: [Theme]
Current=lubuntu
Restart SDDM Using sudo systemctl restart sddm
Themes are usually stored in: /usr/share/sddm/themes/
Edit the SDDM config file: with sudo nano /etc/sddm.conf If the file doesn’t exist, create it and add: [Theme]
Current=lubuntu
Or use the command sudo sddm --example-config > /etc/sddm.conf
Restart SDDM sudo systemctl restart sddm
You can Also go to settings then startup and shutdown then login screen sddm then click lubuntu then apply
Install Firefox with sudo apt update
sudo apt install firefox
if you cant install firefox you can install other browsers like konqueror sudo apt install konqueror
22 Enable The Login And Logout Sound Open System Settings Then Personalization Then Notification Then Application-specific settings then configure then system services plasma workspace configure events then click Play a sound on login and logout sounds
23 Set ascii_distro="none" on nano ~/.config/neofetch/config.conf Because We Dont Need Neofetch Logo
24 Change the Link Open the os-release file sudo nano /etc/os-release
Find the line that looks like this: HOME_URL="https://www.ubuntu.com/"
Replace it to HOME_URL="https://github.com/Haikal02-alt/Triaxis-GNU-Linux"
Then Pretty Name And Name To Triaxis then Change Version_id and version to 2026.1.08
(Optional) You can also change other fields:
NAME="Triaxis"
PRETTY_NAME="Triaxis GNU/Linux"
ID=triaxis
VERSION="2026.1.08"
VERSION_ID="2026.1.08"
VERSION_CODENAME=noble to VERSION_CODENAME=
Save and exit (CTRL+O, CTRL+X in nano).
Restart Plasma session (log out and back in, or reboot).
Now, when you open About System, the link will point to your GitHub page.

For Base Install
sudo nano /etc/os-release
then rename id=ubuntu to id=triaxis
then sudo nano /etc/issue then change The Name Ubuntu 24.04.3 LTS To Triaxis GNU/Linux
then sudo nano /etc/issue.net then rename Ubuntu 24.04.3 LTS To Triaxis GNU/Linux
Then type sudo reboot Or type logout

For Beginners
Use Ubuntu Server Installer

25 Have Fun And Start Using Triaxis And You can Say I USE Triaxis BTW
